  "prompt": "What is child marriage?",
  "response": "Child marriage is a practice where a person under the age of 18 is married, often without their consent. It predominantly affects girls and is considered a human rights violation. In many cases, child marriage leads to:\n\n1. Interruption of education\n2. Higher risk of domestic violence\n3. Early pregnancy and health complications\n4. Limited economic and social opportunities\n5. Increased vulnerability to poverty\n\nChild marriage is most common in developing countries, particularly in parts of Africa, South Asia, and the Middle East. It is often driven by poverty, cultural traditions, gender inequality, and lack of educational opportunities.",
